Male: Tergite VIII with arcuate apex (
Fig. 27J
). Sternite VIII with moderately wide, obtusely triangular medioapical emargination, partly filled by semimembranous extension (
Fig. 27F
). Genital segment with stylus of tergite IX simple, densely setose apically (
Fig. 27G
). Sternite IX with asymmetrical basal portion, apex deeply emarginate, each lobe prolong, forming modified rod-like extensions (
Fig. 27E
). Tergite X triangular, widely emarginate at apex, with variable number of apical setae (
Fig. 27L
).

Aedeagus with median lobe slightly exceeding paramere, narrowed into subrounded apex (
Fig. 27A
); in lateral view, apical portion distinctly bent dorsad (parameral side) (
Fig. 27B
); paramere slightly narrower median lobe, narrowed into obtusely rounded or subtruncated apex, face adjacent to median lobe with peg setae irregularly arranged along apical portion of paramere (
Fig. 27C, D
).

Female: Sternite VIII with arcuate apex, lacking medioapical emargination (
Fig. 27K
). Genital segment with second gonocoxites moderately long, each with minute stylus bearing two long apical setae (
Fig. 27H
). Tergite X triangular, subrounded at apex, with variable number of apical setae (
Fig. 27I
).
